                            <comment id="162135" author="pjones" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2016 22:13:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s what the always_except lable is used for atm &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="162133" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2016 21:57:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I purpose that a special tracker ticket be created that covers all the excepted test. This way these types of tickets will not get lost.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="162114" author="adilger" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2016 20:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, I&apos;m appreciative that you are closing old tickets, but in this case (maybe others) that are marked &quot;&lt;tt&gt;always_except&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; it means the test that is failing has been excluded from the test list, but as James Nunez reported for 2.8.0 the test is still failing, and it does not mean that this bug is fixed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either the test needs to be fixed by a code or test script fix, or if the decision is that the tested functionality is obsolete then the test should be removed completely. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
